#### **D. WorkOrderService**

**File:** `C:\Users\hp\Desktop\eaglepoint\task_90\repo\src\main\java\com\example\ricms\service\WorkOrderService.java`

**Purpose:** Full work order lifecycle management with cost locking, SLA tracking, ratings, and CSV export

**Key Methods:**
- `createWorkOrder(request, actorId)` - Creates work order with attachments (Q1)
- `claimWorkOrder(workOrderId, technicianId)` - Pessimistic locking prevents double-claim
- `addEvent(workOrderId, type, payload, actorId)` - Tracks status transitions; locks cost on RESOLUTION_CONFIRMED (Q12)
- `updateCost(workOrderId, request, actorId)` - Cost editable only before RESOLVED state
- `submitRating(workOrderId, request, userId)` - Rating submission with duplicate guard
- `getAnalytics(from, to, technicianId, statusStr)` - RLS: non-admins see only their own work orders
- `exportCsv()` - Admin-only CSV export with headers: ID, Number, Status, Technician, Created

**Export Code (lines 291-309):**
```java
public byte[] exportCsv() {
    permissionEnforcer.require("ADMIN", "READ");
    List<WorkOrder> all = workOrderRepository.findAll();
    try (StringWriter sw = new StringWriter(); CSVWriter writer = new CSVWriter(sw)) {
        writer.writeNext(new String[]{"ID", "Number", "Status", "Technician", "Created"});
        for (WorkOrder wo : all) {
            writer.writeNext(new String[]{
                    wo.getId().toString(),
                    wo.getWorkOrderNumber(),
                    wo.getStatus().name(),
                    wo.getTechnicianUserId() != null ? wo.getTechnicianUserId().toString() : "",
                    wo.getCreatedAt().toString()
            });
        }
        return sw.toString().getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8);
    } catch (Exception e) {
        throw new AppException("EXPORT_FAILED", "Failed to export CSV", HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR, e);
    }
}
```

#### **E. Idempotency Implementation (OrderService)**

**File:** `C:\Users\hp\Desktop\eaglepoint\task_90\repo\src\main\java\com\example\ricms\service\OrderService.java`

**Purpose:** Time-windowed idempotency on order placement (Q8)

**Key Code (lines 71-85):**
```java
public OrderPlacementResult placeOrder(PlaceOrderRequest request, String idempotencyKey) {
    permissionEnforcer.require("ORDER", "WRITE");
    // C) Time-windowed idempotency — DB unique constraint was dropped in V6.
    //    Return replay=true (HTTP 200) if the same key was used within 10 min.
    if (idempotencyKey != null && !idempotencyKey.isBlank()) {
        String keyHash = hashIdempotencyKey(request.getBuyerId(), idempotencyKey);
        Optional<Order> existing = orderRepository.findByBuyerUserIdAndIdempotencyKeyHash(
                request.getBuyerId(), keyHash);
        if (existing.isPresent()) {
            Order existingOrder = existing.get();
            if (existingOrder.getCreatedAt().isAfter(OffsetDateTime.now().minusMinutes(10))) {
                return new OrderPlacementResult(toResponse(existingOrder), true);
            }
        }
    }
    // ... proceed with new order creation
}
```

